# Case-Centric UI/UX Refactor Plan

## Part A: Codebase Analysis
- [ ] Map existing routes in App.tsx
- [ ] Map existing navigation in _nav.ts
- [ ] Analyze existing pages (Performance, Attrition, Fairness, Interventions, Recommendations, etc.)
- [ ] Identify which modules to reuse, refactor, or create
- [ ] Establish initial implementation plan for missing centers

## Part B: Navigation & Routing Refactor
- [ ] Update [_nav.ts](file:///d:/%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/14-2-2026/2026-2-13/smart_performance_system/client/src/components/layout/_nav.ts) to match the new 15-item IA grouped structure
- [ ] Update [App.tsx](file:///d:/%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/14-2-2026/2026-2-13/smart_performance_system/client/src/App.tsx) routes to support the new IA while preserving existing aliases
- [ ] Ensure Arabic RTL labels and RBAC configurations match

## Part C: Implement Core Centers
- [ ] Create `Alerts Center` (Main page, All, Unread, High Severity, Acknowledged)
- [ ] Create `Alert Details` Drawer (Summary, Signal, Action, Open Case)
- [ ] Create `Case Management Center` (Open, In Progress, Review, Closed)
- [ ] Create `Case Details` Page/Drawer (Summary, Signals, Actions, Monitoring, Impact, Timeline)

## Part D: Refactor Existing Modules
- [ ] Employees: Add Open Case action from profile/list
- [ ] Performance: Link underperformance to Case creation
- [ ] Attrition: Link risk list to Case creation
- [ ] Training: Link training needs to Cases
- [ ] Fairness: Link fairness reports to Cases (Admin)
- [ ] Recommendations/What-If: Allow "Approve scenario" to open Case
- [ ] Impact Analysis: Ensure it visualizes case/intervention impact
- [ ] Create Data Quality module (mock scan, UI for missing values)
- [ ] Update Settings & Users layout alignment

## Part E: Review & Polish
- [ ] Ensure no dead empty buttons (use state/navigation)
- [ ] Verify RTL support
- [ ] Verify Types (`Alert`, `Case`, `Signal`, etc.)
- [ ] Pass all Acceptance Tests

## Part F: Changelog Generation
- [ ] Create `docs/client-ui-refactor-changelog.md`
